	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just another one of my Thougts.. hehe. Bare with me...<br><br>When I first started playing EQ back in April of 2002, I was told you couldnt Alt-Tab out of the Game because of the fact it would close out the game on you. When i questioned this as to why, i was told by Guides that it was to stop people from using Outside Programs to cheat on the game. Do they Honestly think that this will stop because they Blocked Alt-Tab'ing before? They Panic themselves with cheaters on EQ, But Yet they start allowing Alt Tabing out of the game. I dont get it.<br><br>Also, I watched an argument between a Guide and a Player that EQ windows was consitered a 3rd party program and was against EQ rules to use, But now, its allowed. Did Sony just give up on preventing cheating on EQ? Im sure everyone else who has a grip on reality knows that this is going to bring a new set of problems to EQ with people using 3rd party programs.<br><br>Is Sony Honestly this Ignorant? If someone that is a Guide or something, can you tell me What Sony was thinking? I think its Cool to be able to Access the web while playing EQ now, But also, its not, becuase of the Fact that there is going to be so many problems with people Hacking EQ with Programs.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tluadan DrakeSlayer<br>59th Season Preserver<br>&lt;Arctic Flame&gt;<br>-----------------------<br>Freight Turazz<br>36th Ring Paladin<br>&lt;Arctic Flame&gt;</td></tr>
