	   <tr><td colspan=2>Let me tell you something. If you think Sony gives a rats ass about the rules of this game anymore, you're wrong. Lots of offensses that could get a person banned are now allowed or if they are not allowed, violations are overlooked. I found out recently that corpse camping on PvP servers is now legal. They can CC you right up to the point where your corpse expires, but they have to let you loot it before it vanishes, then they can PK you again and CC some more. Bind rushing,kill stealing, intentionally training mobs into others,deliberately causing xp loss and many other &quot;violations&quot; are still illegal, but good luck trying to get a GM to answer your petition with the new customer service system, and if you do get one, they will tell you they can't do anything unless they actually see it happening. Do whatever you want in-game, the odds of getting caught are slim, and even if you do, Sony still wants your money every month so you likely will not get more than a slap on the wrist. <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Jan 11 19:27:03 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br>If you were me and I were you, would we still be friends?</td></tr>
